data.title: Au Lac
data.text:
Delicious plant-based creations with Vietnamese roots and fusion flavors.

In the news

"One of the oldest all-vegan restaurants in the county remains the best."

— OC Weekly

"Everything here is vegetarian, but it makes no difference — the food is universally good."

— District Greater Long Beach

“It’s here that I discovered the real joys of vegan food—playful symphonies of textures, tastes, and visuals.”

— Westways

“It’s not easy to find such a glamorous vegan dining experience in L.A. that won’t break the bank. I love the raw curried rice and the salt and pepper yam 'shrimp'.”

— Dita von Teese, The Infatuation

"Best Vegan Restaurant" - OC Weekly (2008 & 2014)

"9 Best Vietnamese Dishes in Los Angeles" - CBS Los Angeles (2016)

"The Five Best Vegan-Friendly Restaurants in Orange County" - CBS Los Angeles (2012)

"Best Asian Food" - Orange Coast Magazine (2012)
